Mineclearer Version 1.00 4/23/2021
--------Author(s)---------
Simeon Steward simeon@iastate.edu

Referenced and borrowed RLG327 code from my 1.09 solution which is based on the proffesor Scheaffer's 1.08 solution  
Based off of the classic game minesweeper
--------Usage notes--------
use $make to compile the program

./minesweeper runs the program

--numbomb <numBombs> creates the board with the specified number of bomb
            default is 200


--------Controls---------
7 or y:         move upper left
8 or k:         move up
9 or u:         move upper right
6 or l:         move right
3 or n:         move move low right
2 or j:         move down
1 or b:         move low left
4 or h:         move left
Q or q:         quit
f:              toggle flag
g:              guess, if bomb is there, game over
--------Bugs---------